OL,3,CBill on assisted dying faces key vote
OL,4,Cat Scottish Parliament
OL,6,FBoth First Minister John Swinney and
OL,7,FDeputy First Minister Kate Forbes have
OL,8,Falready said they will vote against
OL,9,Fthe Bill, as has Scottish Labour
OL,10,Fleader Anas Sarwar.
OL,12,FIt comes as critics fear the proposals
OL,13,Fcould leave disabled people and
OL,14,Fvulnerable Scots feeling under
OL,15,Fpressure to prematurely end their
OL,16,Flives.
OL,18,FMr McArthur, however, insists the
OL,19,Flegislation would have "strict
OL,20,Feligibility criteria" with proposals
OL,21,Falso "robustly safeguarded".
