OL,6,FHe said that MSPs "must, at the very
OL,7,Fleast, allow time for amendments to be
OL,8,Fconsidered to see if a Bill can be
OL,9,Fagreed that commands majority support
OL,10,Fand public confidence".
OL,12,FHe added: "To my MSP colleagues, I
OL,13,Fsay, if you have not yet made up your
OL,14,Fmind, my door is always open.
OL,16,F"But, most importantly, I would urge
OL,17,Fyou to listen to the voices of
OL,18,Fterminally ill Scots desperate for
OL,19,Fmore choice, control and dignity.
